signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Successful quarterbacks stay cool and stand confidently against the blitz. When they enter the zone, all blitzing linebackers and defensive backs are highlighted after the snap.
Passers with this ability have a higher chance of completing a pass animation (and throwing the ball) while being sacked.
Ballcarriers with this ability have more powerful truck animations.
Midway through the fourth quarter in close games, players with this ability can easily enter (and remain in) the Zone.
Passers with this ability have an increased success rate when using pump fakes on double-move routes against zone coverage.
Aggressive receivers overpower defenders and attack the football. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on aggressive catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running curl or comeback routes.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running post routes.
The game's top defenders excel in all situations. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance of defeating run blocks, tackling runners, and disrupting catches.
Defenders with this ability can still tackle effectively while trying to strip the football.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in zone coverage.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Defenders with this ability play tighter coverage and force more catch knockouts in both man-to-man and zone.
Defenders with this ability have an increased success rate when using conservative or diving tackles.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running slant routes.
